pyspark.sql.functions.sign

Computes the signum of the given value.

Parameters
col : Column or str
          target column to compute on.

Returns : Column
          the column for computed results.

Examples

spark.range(1).select(sign(lit(-5)), sign(lit(6))).show()

+--------+-------+
|sign(-5)|sign(6)|
+--------+-------+
|    -1.0|    1.0|
+--------+-------+
